The dynamical model of a smart structure is developed under the following three assumptions (Xue and Tang, 2006):


There is not any relative motion in the bonding between the beam and the piezoelectric actuator;

The piezoelectric actuator is z–x cut;

The optical axis of the piezoelectric actuator is the thickness direction of beam.

The transversal displacement of the beam can be expressed as equation (6),
(6)uz(x,t)={N}{q}
Where {q} is generalized nodal coordinates vector and {N} is shape functions vector. So
(7)x1=[H][L]{N}{q}={B}{q}
Where {B}=[H][L]{N}, [H] is the matrix that stores the truncated constants matrix from equation (1), [L] is the matrix where all of the displacement field relations are truncated.

The kinetic energy of the smart structure can be written as
(8)Ek=12{q·}T(∫0he∫0leρw{N}T{N}dxdz){q·}
Where ρ and w are the density and width of the element respectively.

Substituting equation (15) into equation (14) and considering the reference input, the closed loop system is written as
(16){χ·=([A]-{I}{K}){χ}+{I}ry={F}{χ}
Where r is reference input.
